author: CBC News
title: Toronto Blue Jays look for Game 6 win to stay alive in ALCS
text:
Live Blog Toronto Blue Jays look for Game 6 win to stay alive in ALCS Toronto fans anxious ahead of Game 6 against the Royals, which starts at 8 p.m. ET in Kansas City CBC News Posted: Oct 23, 2015 5:57 PM ET Last Updated: Oct 23, 2015 8:57 PM ET Related Stories Blue Jays try to force deciding Game 7 vs Royals in ALCS 
Can the Toronto Blue Jays force a Game 7? 
The Jays send David Price to the mound in Kansas City in Game 6, which is the team's second do-or-die game in a row in the best-of-seven American League Championship Series. 
Tonight's game gets underway at 8:07 p.m. ET.
